## 🌱 Introduction

This repository contains **Zihntech Landing Page**, one of the earliest projects in my frontend development journey at **Zihntech Academy**.

At first glance, it may look like a simple landing page. But for me, it represents something much deeper: **the moment I stopped only consuming technology and started building with it**.

Every line of code in this project reflects the experience of a beginner learning how real-world web applications are structured, styled, organized, and version-controlled. This repository is not just about creating a webpage — it is about building **discipline, consistency, problem-solving ability, and confidence as a developer**.

I chose to keep this project public because I believe growth should be visible. Future versions of this repository will become a timeline of my improvement as I continue learning and refining my skills.

---

## 💡 Why This Project Matters

Many new developers are afraid to publish their first projects because they think the code is not perfect.

I had that fear too.

But I realized that **perfection is not the requirement for growth — consistency is**.

This project is my decision to **learn in public**.

Instead of waiting until I become “good enough,” I decided to document the journey from the beginning. I want anyone who visits this repository to see not only the final result, but also the mindset behind it: **show up, build, make mistakes, improve, repeat**.

---

## 🎯 Project Overview

**Zihntech Landing Page** is a responsive landing page designed to practice core frontend development concepts without relying heavily on frameworks.

### The project focuses on:

* Semantic HTML structure
* Responsive CSS layouts
* JavaScript interactivity
* Clean project organization
* Git and GitHub workflow
* Real-world documentation practices

